{
  "texts": [
    "This test set comprised 30 days (720 h) of data covering the remaining part of the dataset.",
    "As previously mentioned, the proposed reward function was designed to focus on the three primary factors of an efficient trading strategy.",
    "To strike a balance between these factors, three distinct thresholds were established for risk management by varying the allowed risk levels: 30% (low), 55% (medium), and 80% (high).",
    "Three other thresholds were defined for active trading by varying the number of permitted active trades per day: up to 8, 16, and 24 times.",
    "The Main-DQN model was trained separately for each case, and the ROI and SR values were obtained."
  ]
}